  "rationale": "Repair keeps the whole locked-style structure that passed and only removes the render-time KeyError by eliminating every content-block (its optional 'body' slot triggered KeyError: 'body'); each text unit now binds through header blocks and known primitive/feature-item keys. Ordering follows the brief's scroll: an inverse hero bookend (the ONLY inverse, ONLY accent, sanctioned display-title-over-media with the seeded overlap/stagger), then all-primary/panel editorial runs. offGridExpansion is LOCKED, so every non-hero section is reuse/adapt with a real seededFrom and carries only baseline-legal identity treatments (ghost-word, marginal-caption) \u2014 no stagger/overlap/bleed off-grid. Heritage uses a panel surface so its bounded era cells stay legal under no-cards-on-cream. Ghost words (ABOUT, MISSION, 1941/2023) sit low-opacity behind content per the brief's outline typography, and no accent appears on any light surface."
